<DocsLayout
  current="benchmarking"
  title="Benchmarking"
  description="Reproduce torana's benchmark numbers yourself with the Docker harness that compares it against Caddy and nginx side by side."
>
  <h1>Benchmarking</h1>
  <p class="docs-sub">A reproducible harness, not a one-time number.</p>

  <p>The repo ships a reproducible harness: torana, Caddy, and nginx side by side in one Docker network, all proxying the same backend, load-generated by fortio.</p>

  <CodeBlock
    label="run it"
    copy={"./bench/bench.sh\nDURATION=30s CONNS=128 ./bench/bench.sh\ndocker compose -f bench/docker-compose.yml down"}
  ><Fragment set:html={`./bench/bench.sh                        <span class="cm"># 15s per target, 64 conns</span>
DURATION=30s CONNS=128 ./bench/bench.sh <span class="cm"># heavier run</span>
docker compose -f bench/docker-compose.yml down`} /></CodeBlock>

  <p>It reports throughput, p50/p99 latency, idle memory after load, and image sizes. Docker on macOS runs in a VM — treat results as a relative comparison; absolute numbers are better on Linux bare metal. See <a href="https://github.com/abhinavcdev/torana/blob/main/bench/README.md">bench/README.md</a> for the full methodology and sample runs.</p>

  <p>Next: <a href="../troubleshooting/">troubleshooting</a>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
